HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 524
By Hale
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Carla Parker on her
selection as the 2024-2025 Cannon County
School District Grades 5-8 Teacher of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to
specially recognize those outstanding teachers who have devoted their careers to providing the
highest-quality education for Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, Carla Parker is one such estimable educator, who has distinguished herself
as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Parker has been selected as the 2024-2025 Cannon County School
District Grades 5-8 Teacher of the Year, a most befitting honor that recognizes the positive
influence she has on so many young lives; and
WHEREAS, Carla Parker is a sixth-grade teacher at Cannon County Middle School,
having taught for twenty-one years in total; in addition to her work in the classroom, she has
been a Beta Club sponsor, a member of the school's medical response team, a Capturing Kids'
Hearts Process Champion, a volunteer with WeCareCannon, and a member of the Cannon
County Senior Center Advisory Board; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Parker, wishing to provide all students with equal access to quality
education, has generously given of her time to help the AmeriCorps program serve
disadvantaged youth, working to secure for every young person the same possibilities and
bright futures as their peers; and
WHEREAS, steeping herself in further study to better her teaching, Mrs. Parker
graduated from Middle Tennessee State University with a bachelor's degree and is currently
earning her Master of Arts in Educational Leadership from Tennessee State University; and
